statement.tex:
\text{Show that the tangents to the curve} \\
y = 7x^3 + 11\text{ at the points where }x=-2 \\
\text{and }x=2\text{ are parallel.}

step.reason:
\text{For two lines to be parallel, their slopes}\\
\text{must be equal }(m_1 = m_2). \\ 
m_1\cdot m_2 = -1\implies\text{ perpendicularity.}

step.tex:
\textbf{Yes. }\dfrac{dy}{dx} = 21x^2\text{ is the same at }x=\pm 5.\\
\text{Hence, for this curve, the tangents at }x=\pm 5\\
\text{would also be parallel.}
